org.geppetto.simulation.visitor

Class CreateModelInterpreterServicesVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • org.geppetto.model.types.util.TypesSwitch<java.lang.Object>
        • org.geppetto.simulation.visitor.CreateModelInterpreterServicesVisitor

  • public class CreateModelInterpreterServicesVisitor
extends TypesSwitch<java.lang.Object>
    This visitor discovers and instantiates the services for each model interpreter. A thread is used to instantiate the services so that a new instance of the services is created at each time (the services use a ThreadScope). A new model interpreter is created for a given library only if it doesn't already exists in the modelInterpreters map
    Author:
    matteocantarelli
